text.tspan: Stress Reactions: Respondents were provided with multiple checkboxes listing stress
reactions students may have experienced due to academic stress during the lockdown.
These choices were based on research conducted by Deb et al. (2015), Parikh et al.
(2019), and Verma et al. (2002). An open-ended answer was included for responses not
included in the choices. This section also posed a 10-point Likert scale analysis
inquiring how the frequency of such events has changed compared to pre-lockdown
conditions
Coping Strategies: Similar to the section for stress reactions, respondents were given
multiple checkboxes for coping strategies they might have engaged in to help alleviate
stress. These choices were based on research conducted by Bhargava and Tiwari
(2019) and Parikh et al. (2019). An open-ended answer was included for responses not
included in the choices. Lastly, respondents were asked how the COVID-19 lockdown
has affected their coping strategies as compared to pre-lockdown conditions.
The online survey took 5-10 minutes to complete. The survey was forwarded to
approximately 650 students and received responses from 220 students, achieving a response rate
The researcher acknowledges that 86.8% (191) of the respondents are students from a
select private day-cum-boarding co-ed high school in Indore, affiliated with the Central Board of
Secondary Education (CBSE). Thus, the sample size may be non-representative of the general
population. Also, as the online survey was forwarded only to contacts of the researcher and the
researcher's school teachers, the result may be biased towards a particular segment of society.
